Mozambican President Filipe Nyusi's son has allegedly pulled a Grace Mugabe-like stunt on the son of a Gauteng MEC and ANC heavyweight in two separate incidents in Joburg last week. Florindo Filipe Jacinto Nyusi allegedly assaulted the MEC's son, Dr Amogelang Manganyi, and smashed his cellphone at a top Sandton restaurant before threatening to blast his brains out with a gun. After the fight, Jacinto allegedly added salt to the wound by hurling about R2,000 at Manganyi and screamed at him to go repair his cellphone. TO READ MORE ON THIS STORY GET A COPY OF TODAY'S SUNDAY WORLD